The paper deals with information theory, coding theory, and network coding, which are all subfields of computer science. The paper establishes a duality result between linear index coding and Locally Repairable Codes (LRCs), which are topics related to information theory and coding theory. The paper also proposes a new upper bound for the multiple unicast network coding problem, which is a topic related to network coding. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.IT (Information Theory). Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
